1. How map differs from other collection interface? Explain with an example program.

   Map is an Object that store in data in key values pair.unique keys associated in single value .it's part of java collection Frameworks.but does not extend to collection interface.
you must used in concrete implementation to create map object.

Sample Program :
    
import java.util.HashMap;
